2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
170 g Vegetable Mix
1 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
4 tbsp Hoisin Sauce
¼ cup Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
1 unit(s) Peanut Butter
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
7 g Black Sesame Seeds
0.06 tsp Pepper*
2 tsp Oil*
1 tbsp Butter*
0.06 tsp Salt*

Cut bok choy into 1-inch pieces. (TIP: Rinse bok choy leaves to wash away any hidden dirt!)
Cut any large broccoli florets into bite-sized pieces.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Add peanut butter and 1/3 cup (2/3 cup) warm water to a medium bowl. Whisk until smooth.
Add soy sauce, vegetarian oyster sauce and hoisin sauce. Whisk to combine.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp butter. Swirl the pan until melted, 30 sec.
Add bok choy and vegetable mix. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until tender-crisp, 3-4 min. Transfer to a plate.

Meanwhile, add chow mein noodles to the boiling water. Cook uncovered, until tender, 1-2 min.
Drain noodles, then rinse under warm water.
Return noodles to the same pot, off heat. Add 2 tsp (4 tsp) oil, then toss gently to coat.
Using a pair of scissors, make a few cuts in the pot to cut up noodles. Set aside.

Return the same pan to medium-high.
When hot, add Beyond Meat® patties to the dry pan.
Cook, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**
Add garlic and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 30 sec.
Add veggies and sauce mixture. Stir to combine.

Add noodles to the pan with Beyond Meat® and veggies. Stir to coat.
Divide noodles between bowls.
Sprinkle sesame seeds over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook it the same way as the beef and pork mix, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.**